data.enText: any very dirty and unpleasant substance

data.chText: 地板上满是油垢和污物。
data.enText: The floor was covered in grease and filth.
words, magazines, etc. that are connected with sex and that are considered very rude and offensive

data.chText: 你怎么能看这种淫秽读物？
data.enText: How can you read such filth?
an offensive word for the police

tr: an offensive or indecent word or phrase
a state characterized by foul or disgusting dirt and refuse
the state of being covered with unclean things
any substance considered disgustingly foul or unpleasant

value.def: Filth is a disgusting amount of dirt.

example.ex: The living-room floor was littered with filth and tin cans...
example.tran: 客厅地上丢满了脏东西和罐头听。

example.ex: Thousands of tons of filth and sewage pour into the Ganges every day.
example.tran: 每天都有成千上万吨污物和废水排入恒河。

value.def: People refer to words or pictures, usually ones relating to sex, as filth when they think they are very disgusting and rude.

example.ex: The dialogue was all filth and innuendo.
example.tran: 这段对话全是下流的言辞和性暗示。
